{"session_id":"svc-1778160661972739053","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-07T13:31:04.00222185Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-e32a0f68-20260507T133059-69668705","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260507T133059-69668705/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260507T133059-69668705/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If you write `.ddx/executions/20260507T133059-69668705/no_changes_rationale.txt`, it MUST carry one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;one-line shell command\u0026gt;` — the loop runs it (cwd = project root, 60s); exit 0 closes the bead, non-zero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: needs_investigation` + `reason: \u0026lt;why\u0026gt;` — bead stays open for triage.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Bare rationales (\u0026#34;nothing to do\u0026#34;) are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260507T133059-69668705/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260507T133059-69668705/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Bead overrides project defaults\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead description and AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and conservative project defaults (YAGNI, DOWITYTD, no-docs-unless-asked) in this worktree — write whatever the bead asks for.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Decomposition depth cap\u0026#xA;This bead is already at decomposition depth 3. Do not create another child layer; if it is still too large, reject the split with a short explanation and write no_changes_rationale.txt instead.\u0026#xA;\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-e32a0f68\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eagent: add enforceable read-only tool reviewer profile\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;The candidate-cycle design requires reviewers to inspect the live attempt worktree efficiently without being able to mutate it. Current reviewer dispatch is not enforced as read-only at the runtime boundary, so moving review into the attempt worktree would depend on prompt wording rather than a hard capability.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_review.go:623-673 builds reviewer AgentRunRuntime with Role=reviewer and MinPower metadata, but no read-only permission profile or tool restriction is set.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:826-842 sets implementation dispatch PermissionsOverride to unrestricted because implementation runs in an isolated worktree; reviewer dispatch needs the opposite boundary.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/service_run.go and related dispatch code are the likely boundary where PermissionsOverride / Role / tool access must be translated into Fizeau execution config.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- Add an enforceable read-only tool reviewer profile to the agent runtime/dispatch boundary.\u0026#xA;- Ensure reviewer role can read files and run read-only inspection commands if supported, but cannot write files, stage, commit, delete, or run mutating shell commands.\u0026#xA;- Fail closed if a harness cannot enforce read-only reviewer mode, with an operator-visible review-error class rather than silently running unrestricted.\u0026#xA;- Add tests with a fake reviewer that attempts mutation and verify the mutation is rejected or impossible.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Do not move review into the attempt worktree in this bead; that is a dependent bead.\u0026#xA;- Do not implement repair cycles.\u0026#xA;- Do not choose concrete provider/model fallback logic.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DEPS\u0026#xA;Depends on the spec bead under this epic so the read-only tool reviewer contract is defined before implementation.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. A runtime/config field or permission profile exists for read-only tool reviewer dispatch and is wired through reviewer execution.\u0026#xA;2. TestReviewerRuntime_ReadOnlyProfilePlumbed verifies BuildReviewExecuteRequest or its replacement sets the read-only reviewer profile for Role=reviewer.\u0026#xA;3. TestReviewerRuntime_MutationDenied uses a fake or script reviewer that attempts to write/stage/commit and proves the attempt is rejected or cannot affect the worktree.\u0026#xA;4. TestReviewerRuntime_UnsupportedReadOnlyFailsClosed verifies unsupported enforcement produces a typed review-error instead of unrestricted review.\u0026#xA;5. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... -run \u0026#34;TestReviewerRuntime_ReadOnlyProfilePlumbed|TestReviewerRuntime_MutationDenied|TestReviewerRuntime_UnsupportedReadOnlyFailsClosed\u0026#34; green.\u0026#xA;6. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... green.\u0026#xA;7. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, area:agent, kind:feature, reliability, adr:024, spec:FEAT-010, candidate-cycle, review\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-31e07fdc\" spec-id=\"FEAT-010\" base-rev=\"c7efe5f15f226d972d111c16daf73767f4c5111b\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260507T133059-69668705\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"FEAT-010\" path=\"docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-010-task-execution.md\"\u003eFeature: Task Execution\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"attempt_id":"20260507T133059-69668705","base_rev":"c7efe5f15f226d972d111c16daf73767f4c5111b","bead_id":"ddx-e32a0f68","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260507T133059-69668705","correlation_id":"ddx-e32a0f68:20260507T133059-69668705","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260507T133059-69668705/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"e